<DIV><STRONG>(Sorry about the tripple post <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-sad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> Don't know what happened.)</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><BR><STRONG>I turned in probably ten-thousands of muffins in the Freeport muffin quest with several different characters a few years ago to make my own faction list. Mine look alot like Skrax list but with some differences.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>I assume turning in 1 muffin (store-bought) would be the smallest faction adjustment in game.<BR>Here is the lenght of each faction from entering it to leaving it:</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>ally:&nbsp; %<BR>warmly: 350 <BR>kindly: 250<BR>amiably: 400<BR>indifferently: 100<BR>apprehensively: 100<BR>dubiously: 400<BR>threathningly:&nbsp; 250<BR>ready to attack:&nbsp;&nbsp; %</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><BR><STRONG>Ally and KoS has no fixed length. Max ally is 2000 hits above your starting faction depending on race/class/diety and max KoS is 2000 below starting faction.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>So max ally is much higher with for example your home town where you start amiably. Some factions where you start out KoS you can never get to ally because its outside 2000 hits. As a high-elf enchanter I have "could not possibly get better" with Legion of Cabilis but Im "only" warmly.<BR></STRONG></DIV>
				
